Output columns (in csv file):

# general
- turn              | int
- subturn           | int
- player_name       | string
- stage             | string -> {IN, OUT}

# player details at specific point
- controlled        | int
- discarded         | int
- in_hand           | int

# played card details
- strength          | float
- attr.water        | int
- attr.fire         | int
- attr.nature       | int
- trait.swift       | bool
- trait.symbiotic   | bool
- trait.poisonous   | bool
- trait.empowering  | bool
- trait.sabotaging  | bool
- trait.supporting  | bool

Output (other file than the above, but the two files are make up the full
result of the simulation):

- game.params:
  - balance         | int
  - deck_size       | int
  - pool_size       | int
  - cards           | int
  - turn_limit      | int
  - leading         | int

- winner
  - name            | string
  - strength        | float

- loser:
  - name            | string
  - strength        | float

- status:
  - code            | int
  - msg             | string
